**Key .NET 11 APIs used:**

| Method | Returns | Throws if missing? |
|--------|---------|-------------------|
| `options.GetTypeInfo<T>()` | `JsonTypeInfo<T>` | ✅ Yes |
| `options.TryGetTypeInfo<T>(out ...)` | `bool` + `JsonTypeInfo<T>?` | ❌ No |

The `TryGetTypeInfo<T>` pattern lets you branch cleanly without try/catch — it returns `false` when the resolver doesn't know about the type (as shown with `int[]` against the limited source-gen context).
